The paper deals with itemset mining, which is a subfield of data mining and database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also heavily relies on Bayesian statistics and machine learning techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves computational methods for sampling models, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
